oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: A view of the construction for the Fort Patrick Henry Dam in the Warrior's Path State Park.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Construction of Fort Patrick Henry Dam began in 1951 and was completed in 1953. The dam is 95 feet high and stretches 737 feet across the South Fork Holston River.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: State parks & reserves; Excavation; Construction; Steam shovels; Reservoirs
